## ğŸ¯ Core Navigation Principles

### 1. Clarity
- Use clear, descriptive labels
- Avoid jargon and internal terminology
- Make links obviously clickable
- Show current location

### 2. Consistency
- Keep navigation in the same place
- Use consistent styling
- Maintain hierarchy across pages
- Predictable interaction patterns

### 3. Simplicity
- Limit top-level items (5-7 maximum)
- Group related items logically
- Use progressive disclosure
- Avoid deep hierarchies (max 3 levels)

### 4. Accessibility
- Keyboard navigable
- Screen reader friendly
- Clear focus indicators
- ARIA landmarks and labels

