## ğŸ“ Key Points

### Must Have
- Clear, descriptive navigation labels
- 5-7 main navigation items maximum
- Active page indicator
- Mobile-friendly menu (hamburger)
- Keyboard accessibility
- Touch-friendly targets (44Ã—44px)
- Consistent placement across pages

### Do
- Use clear, plain language for labels
- Show current location (active states, breadcrumbs)
- Keep navigation in same place on every page
- Test navigation with keyboard only
- Use ARIA labels for screen readers
- Provide multiple ways to navigate (nav, search, breadcrumbs)
- Group related items together
- Test on actual mobile devices

### Don't
- Don't exceed 7 main navigation items
- Don't use jargon or unclear labels
- Don't hide navigation without clear trigger
- Don't rely on hover-only interactions
- Don't make mobile targets too small
- Don't create deep hierarchies (max 3 levels)
- Don't forget skip links for keyboard users
- Don't move navigation between pages

